  "name": "Gunpowder Insight",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The technician gains proficiency with all firearms (except siege weapons) and gains the Gunsmithing feat. If the technician already possesses these abilities via feats or martial talents, he may immediately retrain them.</p>\n<p>In addition, the technician may make the following gadget:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Firework:</strong> This gadget flies in a specific direction and loudly explodes in a color of the technician&#8217;s choice. A firework is considered a splash weapon, but with a range increment of 100 ft. The firework deals 1d6 fire damage per 2 technician levels on a direct hit, and the target must pass a Fortitude save or be blinded for 1 round. On a successful save, the target is still dazzled for 1 round. Creatures within 5 ft. of the target square suffer splash damage equal to the firework&#8217;s minimum damage and are dazzled for 1 round.</li>\n</ul>\n",
